properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 2:11PM CST until January 15 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Freezing Drizzle to Affect Wednesday Morning Commute...

.A quick moving system will bring freezing drizzle and light
freezing rain to the area. This drizzle will spread into the area
from the south and the west early Wednesday morning and last
through the commute. Areas north of Interstate 80 have the best
chance to see freezing drizzle during the morning commute.
Untreated surfaces could become slick.

* WHAT...Freezing drizzle expected. Total ice accumulations up to
a tenth of an inch, although most areas could only see a light glaze
of ice.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, northeast and southeast Iowa
and north central and northwest Illinois.

* WHEN...From 2 AM to noon CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Very slippery sidewalks, roads and bridges are
possible. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning
commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Freezing drizzle is expected to overspread
the area from the south and west Wednesday morning. Eventually
temperatures will rise above freezing from south to north ending
the threat for freezing drizzle. Until this occurs, slick roads
and other surfaces will be possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions.
In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO NOON CST WEDNESDAY
